s who get a chance to review some of the group's projects and think up new ones this year the entourage focuses on reap's work to eradicate childhood anemia and intestinal worms and introduce computer assisted learning in schools related links html+ part 1 taking first steps toward fighting a pervasive parasite http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 2 tackling a malady rooted in extreme poverty http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 3 to a barren plateau to address children's anemia http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 4 solving the anemia problem is one egg enough http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 5 thin soup mattresses of wood and a chance of ghosts http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 6 finding the right mix of information and money to yield results http news stanford edu news 2011 html+ part 7 computers help boost migrant children's grades http news stanford edu news 2011 stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
